<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Hating Awakened Souls is so in right now anyway why hide?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
First of all, hating AS is no trend.  There are PLENTY of valid reasons from training to admitted ebaying that give us all good reason not to like AS.  <br>
<br>
So, with that being said, I want to know what Awakened Souls members think is so GOOD about their guild that they can ignore all the bad things going on and the negative publicity.  <br>
<br>
Not a flame.  I'm seriously interested in what you guys have to say since I have seen nothing from Awakened Souls members with the exception of posts made in defense.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvalquisssilverpalm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 403<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/16/02 7:44:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1223.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The flipside of AS ?</span><hr size=1> I think Captain Roleplay is trying to be neutral and failing.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Still a valid attempt.  I'm rather curious also.<br>
<br>
I've seen a lot of guilds come and go that don't reflect what I would like to really see in FV, but generally the highest standard I apply to any guild is their willingness to be part of the community.  Any time a group of people write off their basic obligations to the community around them, in RL or otherwise, no good can follow.  The most alarming thing I've ever seen was when their guild leader posted something suggesting that Awakened Souls had no interest in the wider community of FV, and intended to stay entirely insulated.  Everything else I can pass over.<br>
<br>
So yes, I'd like to see members of Awakened Souls post here.  Post anything.  Any statement made here that isn't blatently ignorant or hateful is a mark in the favour of AS, as far as I'm concerned, because it signals a willingness to respond to and participate in the community.  Just tell us you are still out there folks, reading the boards, caring what other people think, and that you intend to play with us, not just around us and/or over our dead, trained corpses.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   That's all I personally want to hear.<br>
<br>
Valquiss Silverpalm<br>
