  Don't have much to say on this topic other than I have been with AS a long long time and these people are funny, helpful, talented, smart, caring and concerned about each and every one of us. We are a family, we are friends.<br>
<br>
  on the other hand, what saddens me is well, the bias people have to all of a group for the possible actions of a few or just from hearing rumors, yes I understand why, but to a person like myself who gives so much care, help and just kindness, it really does hurt me to see my friends, and even myself get treated horribly..I do not separate myself from the server, I pride myself on always helping out to be a part of it because I love this server and the people in it...and though AS blatantly states it is not a roleplaying guild, theres a whole lot of us myself included who do, just not in /gu or on raids, and that should not be overlooked, I believe. So please, focus on individuals if you must flame, but don't include the majority, we have feelings too.<br>
<br>
This isnt supposed to be a plea or a whine, I know every time I play Vena, I spend my time helping others, and if people wish to hate me because of a tag there isn't a whole lot I can do about it, but maybe in the end good deeds will be remembered and that is the most I could hope for.<br>
